<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-26T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.61/966a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador to the Polish Government in
                                Exile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-26T16:00:00-04:00">June 26,
                                    1941—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Polish Series No. 14. We have received press reports to the effect that
                            the Polish Government has made certain approaches to the Soviet
                            Government. Any information which you may be able to furnish the
                            Department regarding the nature of these approaches, the circumstances
                            in which they were made, and the character of any reply which may have
                            been received, would be appreciated.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>